the budget unveiled by Finance Minister Trevor Manuel in
parliament earlier Wednesday as "a budget of hope" which would
address equity, redress taxes and create jobs.
</P>
<P>
"I am very hopeful that we are on our way to where our country
should be economically," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the budget, the government will slash personal
income tax and increase spending on education, poverty relief and
job creation in 2000/ 2001.
</P>
<P>
South African Communist Party Chairman Jeremy Cronin said he
was "very pleased" with the budget, particularly with the capital
growth and tax relief.
</P>
<P>
Cronin, however, said that while the budget favored job
creation, "the levels might be a bit restrictive and unrealistic",
and might counter the good intentions that the government had.
</P>
<P>
