<HEADLINE> Eritrean Forces Kill, Wound 200 Ethiopian Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The Eritrean forces have
killed and wounded 200 Ethiopian soldiers, and captured four in
addition to seizing many arms in fresh border conflict after
nine-month lull, the Eritrean News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia launched an attack at dawn Wednesday on the Burie
frontline 70 kilometers west of Assab in southern Eritrea. One
Ethiopian brigade was deployed against Eritrean positions but was
beaten back with heavy causalities, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
It added that the Ethiopian offensive came as U.S. envoy
Anthony Lake and the envoy of the Organization of African Unity
(OAU), Almed Ouyahia, are shuttling between the two Horn of Africa
neighbors to push for the OAU peace plan.
</P>
<P>
Last year during the visits of U.N. envoy Mohammed Sahnoun,
Ethiopia launched similar attacks on Eritrean positions, the
agency noted.
</P>
<P>
Eritrean presidential aide Yemane Ghebremeskel told the agency
that "the Ethiopia has stuck to its pattern of attacking whenever
a peace envoy comes to the region".
</P>
<P>
"Clearly the Ethiopian government wants to extract more
concessions from the peace process by creating this sense of
panic and urgency whenever someone travels to the region," Yemane
added.
</P>
<P>
So far, Eritrea has accepted the OAU peace package while
Ethiopia has objected to the plan.
</P>
<P>
Eritrea and Ethiopia started war over border dispute in May
1998. Since then tens of thousands of soldiers from both sides
have died in conflicts. 
</P>
