<HEADLINE> Sudanese Refugees Doing Farm Work in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Some 3,500 Sudanese
refugees in the Dima Refugee Camp in Gambela, west of Ethiopia,
have begun doing farm work and other productions to improve their
lives, the Ethiopian Herald newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
