About 1,200 Sudanese refugees are engaged in agricultural
activities and 536 in livestock and poultry farming, Camp
Coordinator Zeinu Jemal was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Besides, 1,560 Sudanese refugees who received loans of 28,000
birr (nearly 3,500 U.S. dollars) have launched their own income
generating project in tailoring, knitting, ceramics and trade
activities.
</P>
<P>
According to Neinu, training in health services is also being
given for over 200 Sudanese refugees.
</P>
<P>
There is a plan to distribute seeds and fertilizers to other
refugees to help them start agricultural projects, he said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that there are some 9,500 Sudanese refugees in
the Dima Refugee Camp, which is about 500 km west of Addis Ababa.
</P>
</TEXT>
