<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 24 (Xinhua) -- A record number of patients are
having operations cancelled at the last minute because hospitals
fail to manage beds effectively, according to a report published
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Between 1998 and 1999 cancellations increased by 12 percent to
a total of 56,000 at hospitals in England. One in three hospitals
daily finds it does not have enough beds for patients, the report
by the National Audit Office found.
