<HEADLINE> EU Approves Aid for Relocated Laotian Villagers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said
Thursday it has made available aid worth 1.14 million euros (some
1.14 million U.S. dollars) for Laotian villagers whose relocation
has exposed them to unexpected health hazards.
</P>
<P>
The aid will enable European non-governmental organizations to
improve the availability of food, water and health care pending
more permanent solutions to the situation, the European Union
executive body said.
</P>
<P>
This funding is intended to improve the villagers' access to
clean water and sanitation facilities, as well as to basic health
care. It should also help meet basic food needs as a stepping
stone for a longer-term program to ensure self-sufficiency and
development, the commission said.
</P>
<P>
About 50,000 people are expected to benefit from the aid.
</P>
