<HEADLINE> People's Voices Should Be Heard Constantly: Li Ruihuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Chinese
Communist Party Central Committee, today stressed the necessity to
care for the needs of the broad masses and serve the people
wholeheartedly.
</P>
<P>
During an inspection tour of east China's Zhejiang Province, Li,
also chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), emphasized that the
voice of the people should be heard constantly and regularly.
</P>
<P>
Officials should be grateful to, rather than repulsed by, those
who make criticisms, and they should provide opportunities for
people to speak frankly, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hearing the voices of the broad masses should be a necessary
part of the process of decision making, Li added.
</P>
<P>
The "Three Emphases" drive, especially that at the county-level,
which calls for education in theoretical study, political
awareness, and good conduct, is of great importance to the nation,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that the counties and cities are very important
leadership levels, because they forms a connecting link between
the upper leadership and the townships and countryside.
</P>
<P>
Between February 21 and 24, Li inspected the cities of Yuhang,
Hangzhou, and Jiaxing, and visited enterprises and economic
development zones, and several families of local farmers.
