<HEADLINE> Diplomatic News Highlights (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Following are highlights of
today's diplomatic news released by Xinhua:
</P>
<P>
 China, EU Come Closer in WTO Talks: Long
</P>
<P>
China and the European Union held the latest round of talks on
China's entry into the World Trade Union (WTO) here between
February 21-24.
</P>
<P>
China's chief negotiator Long Yongtu said here tonight
following the conclusion of the talks that China and the EU have "
come very close" after the latest two rounds of talks in Brussels
and Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Long, chief representative for negotiations of the Ministry of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC), said "the Chinese
side thinks that the conditions for ministerial-level talks
between China and the EU have matured. MOFTEC Minister Shi
Guangsheng welcomes Trade Commissioner Pascal Lamy of the European
Commission to visit China, and to finally conclude the China-EU
negotiations on China's entry into the WTO."
</P>
<P>
 Vice-Premier Meets U.S. Secretary of Transportation
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo today expressed the hope that
China and the U.S. will further increase friendly relations and
cooperation in the transportation sector including civil aviation
so as to advance all-round bilateral exchanges and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Wu made this remark during his meeting with visiting U.S.
secretary of Transportation Rodney Slater and his party, who are
here at the invitation of the Civil Aviation Administration of
China after attending an aviation exhibition in Singapore.
</P>
<P>
 China, Russia to Cooperate in Millennium Celebrations
</P>
<P>
China and Russia will cooperate in activities to commemorate
the year 2000 and greet the new century, announced the China 2000
Committee and its Russian counterpart at a press conference in
Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
China 2000 Committee and the Russia 2000 Committee have agreed
to join hands in hosting the "Millennium China Week" in Moscow and
the "Millennium Russia Week" in China, according to Pu Fanzhou,
vice-chairman and secretary general of the Chinese committee.
</P>
<P>
Pu told the conference that activities will fully showcase the
achievements of the Chinese and Russian culture.
</P>
</TEXT>
