<HEADLINE> 10 Tons of Drugs Seized in Iran in 10 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Some 10,141 kilograms of various
kinds of narcotic drugs have been seized in Iran's southern
Hormuzgan Province since March 21, 1999, the Islamic Republic News
Agency reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The drug haul, including opium, hashish, heroin, and opium
extract, showed an increase of 40 percent as compared to the haul
in the last Iranian year ending March March 20, 1999, said
Brigadier General Mohammad Reza Jorkesh, commander of the
provincial law enforcement forces.
</P>
<P>
He added that 5,230 suspects including 1,444 drug addicts were
also rounded up during the period.
</P>
<P>
Some 305 heavy and light vehicles, 68 motorcycles and some
illicit weapons were also confiscated by the forces during several
operations, Jorkesh said. 
</P>
