<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian President Advised to Take Days Off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President
Abdurrahman Wahid has been advised by the presidential medical
team to take a rest for two or three days as he has been suffering
from a bout of flu since Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
Medical team member Dr. Mohammad Tony Soufyan was quoted by the
Antara News Agency as saying the temperature of Wahid's body had
started to reach a normal level at 36 degrees Celsius while his
blood pressure had also improved.
</P>
<P>
State Secretary Marxilam Simandjutak said the president did not
feel well Thursday morning so that the medical team decided to
conduct a total check-up.
</P>
<P>
The examination showed Wahid had had a fever and his body's
temperature had increased but on the whole his condition was fine.
</P>
<P>
Another examination later indicated that the fever had vanished,
Simandjutak added.
</P>
<P>
Since taking office in October last year, Wahid, 59, has often
subjected himself to a punishing daily schedule and long hours in
his attempt to introduce democratic reforms, fix the battered
economy and end several bloody communal conflicts.
</P>
<P>
In addition to extensive tours of many islands across the
country, he's also visited a large number of countries on several
whirlwind diplomatic tours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
