<BODY>
<HEADLINE> D-8 to Promote Private Sector Interaction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Private sector interactions
among the Developing-8 (D-8) could lead them toward prosperity, a
senior official of the Bangladeshi Foreign Ministry said here
Thursday at the end of a two-day session of the D-8 Commission.
</P>
<P>
Additional Foreign Secretary Toufiq Ali told a press briefing
that one of the prime objectives of the forum was to promote
private sector initiatives and interactions among the member
countries.
</P>
<P>
Even though a governmental framework is not yet ready, the
private sectors have already started cooperation. A joint chamber
of commerce and industry, a D-8 federation of technical and
engineering consulting association and a shipping business forum
proposed by Bangladesh have been approved at the commission
session, Ali said.
</P>
<P>
Ali said work is in progress to facilitate trade among the
eight members with harmonization of customs procedures and forms,
smooth banking arrangements and agreements on avoidance of double
taxation.
</P>
<P>
The D-8 group comprises Bangladesh, Egypt, Indonesia, Iran,
Malaysia, Nigeria, Pakistan and Turkey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
