<HEADLINE> China Wins All-around at International Gymnastic Challenge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Zheng Lihui scored
the most to take the men's all-around title at the Australian
International Gymnastics Challenge in Sydney on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Zheng collected a total 56.525 points from six apparatus,
beating from world No.2 Naoya Tsukahara of Japan to second by 0.
050 points.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Yann Cucherat took bronze with 55.675. 
