<HEADLINE> China Cruises to Semifinals of Table Tennis Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 24 (Xinhua) -- China swept into the men'
s semifinals of the 45th World Team Table Tennis Championships
after snatching an easy 3-0 victory over South Korea at Putra
Stadium here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
China's Ma Lin, world number sixth, grabbed the opening point
when he fought back from a game down to beat Kim Taek Soo 21-13,
19-21, 22-20.
</P>
<P>
China's world number three Liu Guoliang then faced no
resistance from Oh Sang Eun as he won the second tie 21-13, 22-20
whilst its top player Kong Linghui, who is world number two,
wrapped up the match with a 21-12, 21-16 win over Ryu Seung Min.
</P>
<P>
"Before the match, we thought that our opponents will give our
players a run for their money as they were out to avenge their
defeats in the semifinals of two previous championships," China's
team manager Cai Zhenhua said.
</P>
<P>
"But, they appeared to lose their rhythm. Of course, we are
very happy to win the quarterfinals as we are just two matches
away from defending our title," he added.
</P>
<P>
China, who won all its five matches in Group A to automatically
advance into the last eight, will now face Japan in the semifinals
Friday. Japan booked its last four berth after it edged Chinese
Taipei 3-2 in another quarterfinal.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Taipei captured the opener when Chiang Peng-lung ousted
Toshio Tasaki in three games 21-16, 12-21, 21-18 but Seiko Iseki
levelled the score as he easily disposed of Chuang Chih-yuan 21-7,
21-12.
</P>
<P>
Koji Matsushita put Japan 2-1 ahead when he needed three games
to outwit Chang Yen-shu 21-19, 19-21, 23-21 but Chinese Taipei's
top player Peng-lung forced the rubber when he scored a narrow 21-
19, 21-16 win over Iseki.
</P>
<P>
Tasaki recovered from his opening match defeat when he sealed
the winning point with a 21-17, 15-21, 21-17 triumph over Chih-
yuan in the decider. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
