<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sale and Pelletier Take Pair Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Jamie Sale and David Pelletier
beat Ina Kyoko and John Zimmerman in a battle between national
champions to win the pair gold medal at the Four Continents Figure
Skating Championships in Osaka on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Sale and Pelletier, the Canadian national champions who led in
Wednesday's short program, received the best marks from nine
judges in the free skating to force American national champions
Kyoko and Zimmerman into second place.
</P>
<P>
Although Sale did not jump her double axel perfectly, they
received perfect 6.0 points from a French judge, five 5.9s, two 5.
8s and a 5.7 in their presentation.
</P>
<P>
"It's fun, it's our first 6.0 out of Canada. It's amazing.
Thank you to the judge who gave it to us," said Pelletier.
</P>
<P>
"We were very, very surprised to get a 6.0. We didn't expect
that at all. Especially from the French judge - it's nice to see
that they enjoyed the performance, even being from another country,
" Sale added.
</P>
<P>
Tiffany Scott and Philip Dulebohn, the US silver medalists,
settled for the third place after coming from fourth place to
surpass Canada's Kristy Sargeant and Kris Wirtz. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
