<HEADLINE> Pioline Cruises into London Indoor Quarter-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Cedric Pioline of France
defeated American Jeff Tarango in straight sets to sail into the
quarter-finals of the London Indoor tennis tournament here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The sixth seed had little trouble in sweeping Tarango 6-3, 6-4
and is to meet either Karol Kucera from Slovakia or fourth seed
Thomas Enqvist of Sweden in the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Pioline, the former Wimbledon and US Open finalist, won the
Rotterdam Indoor title on Sunday by defeating British number one
Tim Henman in three sets in the final. 
</P>
</TEXT>
