<HEADLINE> Seminars in Macao Emphasize One-China Principle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The Association of Returned
Overseas Chinese in Macao and the Association of Chinese Students
of Macao respectively held seminars on Thursday to emphasize the
One-China principle concerning the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
The participants said the One-China principle is the foundation
for and prerequisite to achieving the peaceful reunification of
the country.
</P>
<P>
To safeguard the sovereignty and territorial integrity of China
and promote the reunification of the motherland are the common
aspiration of all Chinese. The Taiwan authorities should bear in
mind the teachings of Dr. Sun Yat-sen and contribute to the unity
and prosperity of the country, rather than act as people condemned
by history, the speakers noted.
</P>
<P>
They said Hong Kong and Macao have returned to the motherland
and set a good example for settling the Taiwan issue on the basis
of the One-China principle. The Taiwan authorities should return
to the One-China stance as soon as possible and any attempt to
separate Taiwan from the motherland can only bring about war and
disaster to the Taiwan people, they warned.
</P>
<P>
The participants noted that the One-China principle of the
Chinese government has won understanding and support from more and
more countries and international organizations.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan compatriots should not be influenced by the small number
of separatists, but should get united with the others of the
Chinese nation to build a stronger country, they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
