<HEADLINE> India Claims to Foil Major Pakistani Intrusion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The Indian military claimed
on Thursday that its border troops foiled a major attempt by
Pakistan to push armed militants into Jammu and Kashmir on
Wednesday night, killing four "Pakistani intruders."
</P>
<P>
The four intruders were killed in the Ramgarh sector of Jammu
region in an exchange of fire with Indian border troops after
their attempt to sneak into Indian territory was exposed, an
official spokesman told the Press Trust of India (PTI) in Srinagar,
capital city of Jammu and Kashmir. The Indian troops suffered no
casualty.
</P>
<P>
In three other separate cases, Indian security forces killed
five militants in different parts of Jammu and Kashmir, the PTI
reported.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, an Indian Border Security Force inspector and a
Special Police officer were killed in Badgam district of central
Kashmir and Sopore area of Baramulla in two separate militant
attacks.
</P>
<P>
Indian police and security forces in Jammu and Kashmir
Wednesday also arrested six other militants while another militant
laid down his arms, said the PTI. 
