<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Favors Re-establishment of Ad Hoc Committee on Outer Space </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, February (Xinhua) -- Russia supports the re-
establishment of the ad hoc committee on the prevention of an arms
race in outer space (PAROS), said a Russian diplomat here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the plenary session of the Conference on
Disarmament (CD) Ambassador Vasily Sidorov said the Russian side
supported the re-establishment of the ad hoc committee on PAROS in
order to elaborate specific practical arrangements that would
block the ways of turning the space around the Earth into a new
arena for power confrontation.
</P>
<P>
"In this respect, we express solidarity with our Chinese
colleagues, who also urge immediate re-establishment in the CD of
an appropriate ad hoc committee on PAROS with a mandate on
elaboration and conclusion of arrangement 'on the prohibition of
testing, deployment and use of weapons and weapon systems as well
as their components in outer space to prevent weaponization of the
outer space'," said Sidorov.
</P>
<P>
He told the session that his delegation was aiming at
constructive cooperation and the search for mutually acceptable
solutions for PAROS subject matters.
</P>
<P>
The Russian ambassador also called on other delegations to show
political flexibility so that the mood for immediate start of the
work in this direction would prevail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000224.0114 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Opposed to U.S. Proposal to Modify ABM Treaty for NMD Deployment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Russia is strongly against a
United States proposal to adapt the 1972 Anti-Ballistic Missile (
ABM) treaty to allow the deployment of the national missile
defense (NMD), said a Russian diplomat here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the plenary session of the Conference on
Disarmament (CD), Ambassador Vasily Sidorov said, "the 1972 ABM
treaty indeed provides for possible changes to its provisions and
that was used by the parties to the treaty in the past. But the
substance of those changes was primarily to enhance the treaty
regime (and) to strengthen its deterrent basis."
</P>
<P>
Talking about the recent U.S. proposal to adapt the ABM treaty
to permit deployment of a "limited" NMD, Sidorov said that the
proposal was contrary to the key provision of Article I of the
treaty which constitutes its substance.
</P>
<P>
"As a result of such treaty transformation, a precedent might
be set in the disarmament practice, when an addition or amendment
to the agreement which limits and curbs the development of most
advanced types of armaments, would convert it into an agreement
that permits to build up military potential," the Russian
ambassador said. "We do not agree with such logic."
</P>
<P>
"If the United States implemented its unilateral plans on NMD,
the ABM treaty would be destroyed," Sidorov warned. "The structure
of treaties and agreements in the field of nuclear disarmament
would crumble along with it."
</P>
<P>
"A serious damage would be made to the whole disarmament
process as well as to the regimes of nonproliferation of WMD (
weapons of mass destruction), missiles and missile technologies,"
he stressed. "Extremely dangerous incentives for triggering an
arms race in outer space would be created." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000224.0115 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NATO Force's Failure Leads to Kosovo Crises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, February 24 (Xinhua) -- An editorial carried by
Greece's Kathimerini daily newspaper on Thursday said that the
NATO-led peacekeeping force in Kosovo should be held responsible
for the increasingly deteriorating situation in the Yugoslav
province of Kosovo, which has seen rising violence between
peacekeepers, ethnic Albanians and Serbs.
</P>
<P>
The editorial said, "The failure, whether intended or not, of
NATO troops in Kosovo, a military force comprising 30,000 men, to
preserve the region's bi-communal status, is a source of crises
that are becoming increasingly hard to control."
</P>
<P>
The editorial also noted that concerns have been intensified by
the fact that NATO supreme commanders are accusing Yugoslav
President Slobodan Milosevic of being responsible for the
worsening situation in the province while NATO troops have done
nothing to prevent the expulsion of thousands of Serbs by Kosovo
Albanians.
</P>
<P>
NATO is gradually also facing the increasing discontent of
ethnic Albanians, who had originally heralded it as their
liberator, the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic Albanians, encouraged by NATO's anti-Serbian stance, are
increasingly tending to view the allied forces as an obstacle to
the immediate independence of Kosovo, a fact which is undercutting
the support for NATO's involvement from the people of the Balkan
region, according to the editorial.
</P>
<P>
The editorial warned that the Balkan region has entered "a
phase of upheaval," in which the consequences are unpredictable.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000224.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Results of Four Continents Figure Skating Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Following are the results of the
Four Continents Figure Skating Championships in Osaka on Thursday:
</P>
<P>
