<HEADLINE> Draw of HK Rugby Sevens Made </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 24 (Xinhua) -- An official draw was made
here on Thursday for the 2000 Hong Kong Rugby Sevens tournament to
be played at the Hong Kong Stadium from March 24 to 26.
</P>
<P>
China, an emerging rugby nation which will be playing in the
tournament for its third consecutive appearance, was polled into
Pool A to face defending champions Fiji.
</P>
<P>
Home team Hong Kong was drawn into Pool C to face another
traditional rugby powerhouse Scotland.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-four teams will be competing in the 2000 Credit Suisse
First Boston Hong Kong Sevens, which has recently become part of
the International Rugby Board's World Sevens Series for the first
time.
</P>
<P>
The 10-stop World Seven Series this season, which opened in
Dubai last December, has finished the first seven stops and will
close in Paris in May.
</P>
