<HEADLINE> U.N. High Commissioner for Human Rights to Visit HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 24 (Xinhua) -- U.N. High Commissioner for
Human Rights Mary Robinson is to pay a half-day visit to the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) on February 29, a
spokesman for the HKSAR government said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that, through meetings with government officials,
members of the Legislative Council and concerned non-government
organizations, Robinson will obtain a more personal understanding
of how human rights are protected here," said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The arrangement for her visit will ensure that she hears as
wide a range of views as possible within the limited time
available, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
Robinson will depart for Beijing the same evening to attend the
8th Workshop on Regional Cooperation for the Promotion and
Protection of Human Rights in the Asia-Pacific Region, which will
take place between March 1 and 3.
</P>
<P>
The trip will be the former Irish president's first to the
HKSAR in her capacity as the U.N. human rights chief. 
</P>
</TEXT>
