<HEADLINE> Non-Communist Party Leaders Support Government's Position on Taiwan Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of China's non-
Communist parties attending a forum here today to discuss the
recent white paper on the Taiwan issue expressed their unwavering
support for the government's policies and position on the issue.
</P>
<P>
The participants said they believe that under the premise of
the one-China principle, the complete reunification of the
motherland is the common will of all Chinese people and all
members of the country's eight non-Communist parties and the All-
China Federation of Industry and Commerce.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Kehui, vice-chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) and
chairman of the Central Committee of the Taiwan Democratic Self-
Government League, presided over today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said the non-Communist parties will continue implementing
the basic principle of "peaceful reunification and one country,
two systems," and President Jiang Zemin's eight-point propositions.
His league will make greater efforts to keep in touch with
compatriots in Taiwan to push forward exchanges between the two
sides in all fields, he said.
</P>
<P>
The white paper, entitled "The One-China Principle and the
Taiwan Issue," contains the government's reiteration of its
position and policies on the issue against a backdrop of growing
and secessionist activities within the island of Taiwan, said Zhou
Tienong, vice-chairman of the CPPCC National Committee.
</P>
<P>
Those who spoke at the forum also included Wu Xiuping, vice-
chairman of the Central Committee of the China Democratic League,
Chen Mingde, secretary-general of the Central Committee of the
China Democratic National Construction Association, Chu Zhuang,
vice-chairman of the Central Committee of the China Association
for Promoting Democracy, Li Meng, vice-chairman of the Central
Committee of the Chinese Peasants and Workers' Democratic Party,
Du Yijin, vice-chairman of the Central Committee of the China Zhi
Gong Party, Hong Fuzeng, vice-chairman of the Central Committee of
the Jiu San Society, Li Minkuan, vice-chairman of the Central
Committee of the Taiwan Democratic Self-Government League, and
Wang Zhiguo, vice-chairman of the All-China Federation for
Industry and Commerce. 
</P>
</TEXT>
