<HEADLINE> German President Lauds Friendly Ties With Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Visiting German President
Johnannes Rau said here on Thursday that Egypt and Germany were
bound by friendly ties in all domains.
</P>
<P>
The German people bear a great interest in Egyptian civilization
and science, and its ancient and modern history, said Rau while
meeting with local press.
</P>
<P>
Rau arrived here Monday on a five-day official visit to Egypt.
He had held talks with his Egyptian counterpart Hosni Mubarak
Wednesday on further promoting bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders discussed, among other things, an array of
regional and international issues. Rau responded positively to an
earlier proposal by Mubarak to set up an Egyptian-German business
forum to increase trade volume between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Later in the day, Rau also met with Secretary General of the
Cairo-based Arab League Ahmed Esmat Abdel-Meguid on the
developments in the Middle East peace process, Arab-German
relations and the current situation in Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
On the establishment of a German university in Egypt, Rau said
contacts between the two sides are proceeding well and the plot of
land for its construction has already been purchased. 
