<HEADLINE> France to Mark Centenary of Birth of Saint-Exupery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 24 (Xinhua) -- France will organize next month
a celebration of the centenary of the birth of pilot and writer
Antoine Saint-Exupery, the author of "Little Prince" and "Night
Flight".
</P>
<P>
The Foundation of Saint-Exupery and the Gallimard publishing
house will organize a national competition of essays on the theme
of "Little Prince" which will be joined by children aged from
eight to 15.
</P>
<P>
An exhibition entitled "Wind, Sand and Stars" which is
dedicated to the life of the writer and pilot will be held in
France, Switzerland, Denmark and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
A plane, christened "the City of Paris", will fly from France
to north Africa and South America along the mail and cargo air
line which was pioneered by Saint-Exupery and his colleagues in
the 1930s.
</P>
<P>
Born in Lyon in 1900, Saint-Exupery died on a military flight
mission from north Africa to occupied France in 1944. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
