<DOCNO> XIE20000224.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Championships to be Split on Trial Basis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The International Table
Tennis Federation (ITTF) Thursday decided to split the World Table
Tennis Championship into the individual and team events after next
year's tournament in Osaka.
</P>
<P>
ITTF president Adam Sharara however said the council also
decided that the split, which would be tried out in the 2003
Championships, would be initially on a trial basis.
</P>
<P>
He said the ITTF executive committee would later decide if the
team and individual championships would be held on the same year
or on alternate years after 2003.
</P>
<P>
It was also decided that some tournaments would be played with
games going up to 11 points while others would have a tie-break at
11 in the decisive game.
</P>
<P>
Other tournaments would also try out a new service rule where
the ball in service must be struck in front of the body, said
Sharara.
</P>
<P>
Decisions to permanently change the scoring system and the
service might be taken only after Osaka meet next year, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
