<HEADLINE> Motorola Welcomed to Expand Business in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Mayor Liu Qi welcomed
the U.S. Motorola Corporation to expand its business in the
Chinese capital during his meeting today with Terry Heng, vice-
president of the corporation.
</P>
<P>
Motorola has close links with Beijing, Liu said, adding that
his city will give priority to the development of software,
information industry, and biological engineering.
</P>
<P>
The Zhongguancun area of Beijing, China's Silicon Valley, has
aroused great interest among both overseas and domestic
businesspeople, and nearly 20 multinationals have established
research and development centers there, the mayor said.
</P>
<P>
Terry Heng said that he came to Beijing to increase investment
and expand his company's software business in China, and that the
relationship between Motorola and China has been going very well.
