<HEADLINE> HK's 18 Banks to Jointly Offer Online Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 24 (Xinhua) -- A new Internet portal site
containing financial products and services of Hong Kong's 18
leading banks will be launched in April, offering consumers a
virtual one-stop shop for their banking needs.
</P>
<P>
The portal site, namely Bankingstreet.net, is developed by
SUNeVision, the technology infrastructure and e-business flagship
of Sun Hung Kai Properties (SHKP), a leading real estate dealer in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Bankingstreet.net will initially provide users with information
about a range of products and services from its partners including
mortgage interest rtes and associated terms and conditions.
</P>
<P>
Users will be able to access information about promotions from
the participating banks, current market news and commentaries,
legal issues relating to banking and personal finance.
</P>
<P>
Other banking and financial services like securities trading,
personal loans, credit cards and deposit rates will also be
provided in near future.
</P>
<P>
The 18 banks that have undertaken to partner with the site
include Bank of China, Citibank, Bank of East Asia, Standard
Chartered Bank, and so on.  
</P>
