<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Leap Over 4 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks soared 681.
87 points, or 4.16 percent to close at 17,058.66 Thursday, after
telecoms shares surged on the overnight record rise at the U.S.
Nasdaq market.
</P>
<P>
China Telecom (Hong Kong) Ltd, the most actively traded stock,
vaulted 9.09 percent or 5.50 HK dollars to 66 HK dollars and made
up just under half of the Hang Seng's gain, according to Reuters
3000.
</P>
<P>
The tech-laden Nasdaq rocketed 168.21 points, or 3.84 percent
to a record 4,550.33 on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 17.998 billion HK dollars (2.3 billion U.S.
dollars), which is 196 million HK dollars (25.1 million U.S.
dollars) more than Wednesday's 17.802 billion HK dollars (2.3
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
All the four sub-indices of the blue-chip Hang Seng Index
received gains with Finance, Utilities, Properties and the
Commerce and Industry rising by 1.90 percent 0.18 percent, 3.24
percent and 5.85 percent.
</P>
<P>
The China-related stocks ended lower with the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index down 2.19 percent and Hang Seng China-Affiliated
Corporations Index down 1.34 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index opened 135.78 points, or 0.83 percent,
higher at 16,512.57 and grew 681.87 points, or 4.16 percent, to
close the morning session at 17,058.66 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
