<HEADLINE> Angola, UNDP Sign Agreement on Program of Social Rehabilitation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LUANDA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Development Program
(UNDP) agreed on the implementation of the program on social
rehabilitation in Angola, official source said here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Angolan Planning Minister Ana Dias Lourenco
who co- signed the agreement with the UNDP representative in
Angola Mesa Zoraida, the program will help improving agricultural
production conditions and stock farming.
</P>
<P>
The program was put forward in 1998 and formalized in last
May. But it has been interrupted for two years by the
recrudescence of the civil conflicts between the Luanda government
and the rebel National Union for the Total Independence of Angola
(UNITA).
</P>
<P>
According to the program, UNDP and the Angolan government will
finance the social projects in Angola in the domain of
agriculture, stock farming, infrastructure and the development of
the small and mid-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Ana Lourenco said that the emersion of the expectation of
peace in the country has opened wide perspective for the
transition from the emergency state to rehabilitation and
development.
</P>
<P>
From 1996 to 1998, UNDP and the Angolan government have
financed some 240 projects at the national level, mainly in the
provinces of Benguela, Huambo, Malange and Uige. 
</P>
</TEXT>
