<HEADLINE> Ericsson Demonstrating 3G Mobile Technology in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Ericsson today demonstrated
its latest third generation (3G) mobile technology in Beijing. The
world's leading telecommunications technology company also is
committed to cooperate with Chinese institutes to promote 3G
technology in China.
</P>
<P>
Mike Ricks, President of Ericsson (China) Company Ltd., said
that his company will actively support China's 3G technology
development and play an important role in China's future
telecommunications market.
</P>
<P>
Described by experts as the "mobile Internet", the 3G
technology will help subscribers access various multimedia
services including mobile graphs.
</P>
<P>
In China, Ericsson has already invested significantly in
promoting 3G technology. In 1999, Ericsson established the Mobile
Communication Technology Research Center at the Beijing Institute
of Technology.
</P>
<P>
The first Mobile Multimedia Open Lab also opened in China last
year, jointly launched by Ericsson, the Beijing Institute of
Technology, the Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications
and the China Mobile Communication Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Ericsson has set up 23 offices and eight joint ventures in
China.  
