<HEADLINE> China to Expand Global Market of Traditional Medicines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- China's pharmaceutical
industry will improve the quality of traditional medicines to
increase its overseas markets.
</P>
<P>
"Traditional Chinese medicines (TCM) will continue to be used
worldwide if modern technology is adopted to develop high-quality
new drugs," said Zhu Qingsheng, director of the State
Administration of Traditional Chinese Medicine.
</P>
<P>
China is the home of about 13,000 kinds of traditional
medicinal materials and the world's largest TCM producer and
consumer.
</P>
<P>
According to experts, Chinese herbal medicines are not selling
very well on the international market due to problems in quality,
packaging and marketing strategies.
</P>
<P>
Despite these problems, Zhu is confident that traditional
Chinese medicine will find a niche on the international market as
natural therapies and medicines have become popular overseas.
</P>
<P>
Zhu's administration is working on a long-term plan to
encourage basic theoretical research, new drug development and
clinical studies in Chinese medicine.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said the World Health Organization (WHO) has played an
active role in stimulating the research and application of
traditional medicines. An international conference on traditional
medicines will be held in Beijing in April hosted by the WHO and
the State Administration of Traditional Chinese Medicine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
