<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Senate Refuses to Recognize Genocide of Armenians by Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The French Senate has refused to
vote for a law recognizing the alleged genocide of Armenians by
Turkey during World War I.
</P>
<P>
In a statement published earlier this week, the Senate which is
dominated by a right-wing majority said that "neither the French
president nor the government want the discussion of this proposal
of law which risks thwarting the process of reconciliation" among
the nations in the southern Caucasus region.
</P>
<P>
The leftwing-dominated French National Assembly has voted a law
to recognize the alleged genocide, in which Armenia said 1.3
million Armenians were killed by Turkish troops.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has rejected the accusation and said 300,000 people died
in the forcible deportation of the Armenians from the Caucasus to
Syria during the war. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
