<HEADLINE> Indonesian President Remains in Good Health: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President
Abdurrahman Wahid remains in good health, State Secretary Marsilam
Simandjutak told reporters here Thursday following news on the
president healthy condition in the morning.
</P>
<P>
"Thanks God, Gus Dur (Abdurrahman Wahid) remains healthy,"
Simandjutak said.
</P>
<P>
He said the president canceled several appointments on Thursday
to undergo a medical check-up.
</P>
<P>
Wahid was scheduled to receive Head of the Supreme Advisory
Council Achmad Tirtosudiro, Head of the Central Bureau of
Statistics Sugito Suwito and Riau Governor Saleh Djasit on
Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
But the schedules were canceled due to medical check-up which
has to be undergone by Wahid, Simandjutak said.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the list of visitors Wahid was scheduled to meet
despite his medical check-up, Simandjutak said: "Secretary of the
president (Ratih Hardjono) does not know that the president should
undergo (medical) check-up."
</P>
<P>
Simandjutak added that in fact the medical check-up has been
scheduled a long time before, but due to his activities such a
check-up was delayed.
</P>
<P>
The president is almost blind following a serious of strokes in
recent years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
