<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Oil Reserves Estimated at 3.63 Bln  Barrels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia, currently
ranked 25th in world petroleum production, has an estimated 3.63
billion barrels of oil and 2.4 trillion cubic meters of gas
reserves, Minister in the Prime Minister's Department Bernard
Dompok said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This is besides the estimated 1.4 billion cubic meters of gas
in the Malaysia-Thailand joint gas fields, he told Parliament here
during Question Time.
</P>
<P>
He said Malaysia's current daily oil production stood at 612,
000 barrels with the peninsula producing 345,000 barrels and the
rest by Sabah and Sarawak, two states in East Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
He said that at the current rate of production the existing oil
reserves could last 15 years and the gas 30 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
