<HEADLINE> Thirsty Monkeys Stone Herdsman to Death in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIRBOI, February 24 (Xinhua) -- A herdsman was stoned to death
by a group of thirsty monkeys in the drought-hit northeastern
Kenya as he watered his livestock, the East African Standard
newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"In a clear sign of worsening drought, a herdsman was killed
after riotous monkeys stoned pastoralists at a watering point in
Wajir District," the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The rare accident occurred at Ajawa trading center in Wajir
North last Saturday, the paper added.
</P>
<P>
The dead, Ali Adam Hussein, was in a group of other
pastoralists who were watering livestock when the monkeys attacked
them.
</P>
<P>
Most parts of Kenya are now hit by severe drought, especially
north and northeastern Kenya.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that there are over two million Kenyans are
suffering from famine across the east African country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
