<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Move Higher in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed higher in
Tokyo Thursday, led mainly by high-priced information and
technology issues.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange gained 51.89 points, or 0.27
percent from Wednesday's close to end at 19,571.44.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, added 22.81 points or 1.37 percent to 1,690.
05.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section decreased to 601.62 million
shares from Wednesday's 678.96 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Sumitomo Osaka Cement was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Leading information and high-tech issues were firm after the
technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index in New York posted its
largest one-day point gain, rising 168.21 points Wednesday to hit
a record closing high of 4,550.33, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Trading firms, brokerage houses and wholesalers also drew
active buying, but mining companies, retailers and nonbank
moneylenders faced selling.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers exceeded
losers 720 to 501, while 131 issues closed unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
