<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Chinese Taipei in Table Tennis Worlds Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 24 (Xinhua) -- China's women's team
entered the finals of the 45th World Team Table Tennis
Championships at the Putra Stadium here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In a Semi-final, China defeated South Korea 3-1.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Wang Nan lost her first game to South Korean Kim Moo
Kyo 19-21, 19-21. But her teammate Li Ju equalized the score by
beating Ryu Ji Hae 21-16, 15-21, 21-19.
</P>
<P>
And Zhang Yining added one point to China to lead the score
table by eliminating Lee Eun Sil 21-12, 21-15.
</P>
<P>
Wang Nan took on Ryu Ji Hae in the fourth game and settled it
21-12, 21-10 in her favor.
</P>
<P>
In the final, China will meet Chinese Taipei who beat Romania 3-
2 in another semi-final here Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
