<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Higher Industrial Growth in Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, February 16 (Xinhua) -- The industrial output value
of Chongqing, the largest metropolis in southwest China,
registered a 18 percent year-on-year rise in 1999, ranking first
in China.
</P>
<P>
The sales rate of industrial products hit 99.7 percent last
year, higher than the national average. As a result, losses
incurred by unprofitable enterprises dropped by 23 percent.
</P>
<P>
Improving market competitiveness and developing new products
are major reasons for the industrial growth, said a government
official.
</P>
<P>
The out put of motor vehicles and motorcycles rose from 37
percent to 43 percent out of the city's total industrial
production last year. The market share of new and high-tech
products such as electronic, biological and environmentally-
friendly products has increased. 
</P>
</TEXT>
