<DOCNO> XIE20000224.0199 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Needy in Chongqing Eradicate Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- In rural Chongqing in
southwest China, which has the largest group of poor farmers in
China, the number of these farmers has been reduced from 3.6
million to one million by the end of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing has a population of some 30 million, 80 percent of
them live in the rural areas of the metropolis. Some 3.66 million
rural people, accounting for 15 percent of the rural population,
lived under the poverty line before the city was upgraded into
China's fourth municipality in 1997.
</P>
<P>
At present, 19 of the 21 poor counties in Chongqing have
eradicated poverty. Over 70 percent of the needy people have
adequate to eat and wear.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Qiya, director of the Municipal Poverty Elimination Office,
said that improvement of their life is due to financial assistance
from all sectors of society and loans.
</P>
<P>
The government of Chongqing organized 21 relief groups
providing farmers with funds, technology and information for
developing local tourist resources, herbal medicine processing and
animal husbandry.
</P>
<P>
Local credit co-ops have granted 10 million yuan in small loans
to help 10,000 rural households develop agriculture and facilitate
farm produce processing and transportation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
