<HEADLINE> Vietnamese FM Outlines 3 Goals for Vietnam-China  Relations in 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Implementing the Vietnam-China
Land Border Treaty signed here in December 1999 is one of the
three goals outlined by Vietnam's Foreign Minister Nguyen Dy Nien
to boost the bilateral ties in 2000, local press reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The two remaining goals, Nien said, are to accelerate the
negotiations for an agreement on the delimitation of the Bei Bu
Gulf, to raise two-way trade value to 2 billion U.S. dollars and
carry out agreements reached during the visit to Vietnam by
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji in last December.
</P>
<P>
Nien outlined these goals during his interview with Vietnamese
Communist Party's daily Nhan Dan in anticipation of his three-day
official visit to China from Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It is his first tour abroad since Nien took the post of foreign
minister in late January.
</P>
<P>
Nien stressed that Vietnam and China enjoy four fundamental
advantages to strengthen mutual trust and boost bilateral
friendship and comprehensive cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister said he is optimistic about achieving
above-mentioned targets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
