<DOCNO> XIE20000224.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Industrialist Predicts Death Of Wired Phones In 5 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, February 23 (Xinhua) -- In 5 years most people
will be using wireless telephones for both voice communication and
Internet access, not traditional telephone lines, Irwin Mark
Jacobs, chief executive officer of high-flying mobile phone
technology company Qualcomm Inc. said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"More and more we are going to see a situation where a wire
telephone hooked to a wall will become an object of some surprise,
" Jacobs said at conference held here on the topic of growth
company stocks.
</P>
<P>
San Diego-based Qualcomm, which holds a patent on so-called
CDMA wireless chips, currently has about 50 million subscribers
that use its technology and could add 20-30 million by 2001,
Jacobs said.
</P>
<P>
The technology of CDMA, or code division multiple access, takes
information contained in a signal and spreads it over a wide
bandwidth. More than 75 companies have so far been licensed to use
Qualcomm's technology.
</P>
<P>
"Just 15 years ago people said we would be lucky if there were
over a million subscribers by the turn of the century," Jacobs
noted.
</P>
<P>
But growth has come at a much higher rate due largely to
falling per-minute prices for cell phone usage, Jacobs pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Qualcomm is now working to develop technology for wireless
communication through airlinks to antennas that let electronic
devices like phones, computers and printers communicate with each
other and the Internet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000224.0220 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korean Trade Deficit With Japan Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, February 24 (Xinhua) -- South Korea registered a trade
deficit of 8.3 billion U.S. dollars with Japan in 1999, up from
the previous year's 4.6 billion, the Commerce, Industry and Energy
Ministry said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said South Korea saw a trade surplus of 23.9
billion dollars, a drop of 15.1 billion dollars from 39 billion
dollars in 1998 and that Japan was blamed for the drop.
</P>
<P>
The country's trade deficit with Japan declined every year
until 1998. It fell to  13.1 billion in 1997 from 15.7 billion in
1996 and then to 4.6 billion in 1998.
</P>
<P>
With the Middle East, the country saw deficit growing to 8.3
billion dollars from 4.8 billion dollars due to the rise in oil
prices.
</P>
<P>
However, the nation's surplus with the United States and the
European Union rose.
</P>
<P>
It posted a surplus of 4.6 billion dollars with the United
States last year, up from 2.4 billion dollars in 1998 while its
surplus with the European Union rose to 7.6 billion from 7.2
billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
