<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Leads Nation in Granting Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The amount of outstanding
consumption loans in Shenzhen in south China's Guangdong Province
neighboring Hong Kong was 24.5 billion yuan in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Information from Shenzhen Central Sub-Branch of People's Bank
of China said that the figure made up one quarter of the country's
total consumption loans or about ten percent of various loans in
Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
Commercial banks in Shenzhen have offered a number of new loans
for purchasing cars, refurbishing homes, holidays, education and
consumer durables.
</P>
<P>
By late 1999, the amount of outstanding loans for housing
climbed to 23.3 billion yuan in Shenzhen, 8.3 billion yuan more
than the figure at the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
The amount of outstanding loans for purchasing cars reached 500
million yuan last year while loans for interior home remodeling
and refitting and education climbed to 680 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that setting up a personal credibility appraisal
system will be conducive to the fast growth of granting loans in
Shenzhen.  
</P>
