<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Hero of the Forest" Honored at the Great Hall of the People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- A meeting was held today in
the Great Hall of the People in commemoration of Ma Yongshun, a
late model lumber worker in the northernmost Heilongjiang Province
for his contributions to afforestation in China.
</P>
<P>
Wen Jiabao, a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and Chinese vice-premier,
was among those ranking Chinese Party and Government officials
attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Ma Yongshun, born in 1913, began to work as a lumber-jack in
Heilongjiang's Tieli Forest Center in 1948. From 1959 until his
death on February 10 this year. Ma spent his whole life planting
trees, leaving behind more than 20 hectares of forest.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Vice-Minister of Personnel, Zhang Xuezhong,
read out an eulogy for Ma, who was awarded and commended
posthumously by the China National Greening Committee (CNGC), the
Ministry of Personnel and the State Administration of Forestry (
SAF) as "Hero of the Forest". And SAF Director Wang Zhibao read
out the decision on behalf of both CNGC and SAF to carry out the
activities to learn from Ma.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao called on the people
throughout China to learn from Ma's fine, meritorious work and
take tree-planting and greening the motherland as their common
responsibility and obligation.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Wen urged forestry workers nationwide to put the
nation's interest first and to do a still better job in shifting
their work emphasis from logging to natural forest protection,
afforestation and environment protection so as to achieve
sustainable development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
