<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Garment Sector is Main Job Creator in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The industrial sector,
especially the garment sector, is the main job opportunity
providers in the country, according to a labor analysis made by
the Council for Development of Cambodia (CDC).
</P>
<P>
Since the CDC was established in 1994, the industrial sector
has provided up to 400,000 employment opportunities to locals in
26 categories, ranging from food processing, cement manufacturing
to household goods, garments and wood processing.
</P>
<P>
The analysis showed that the agriculture sector ranked second
in terms of employment with about 35,000 jobs while the services
sector with about 17,200 and tourism with about 11,700 jobs.
</P>
<P>
The garment sector continued to be the main employment creator
in the country with more than 280,000 employers while plantations
provided 27,170 jobs, followed by the shoes industry which created
21,450 jobs and the chemical sector which provided 19,500 jobs.
</P>
<P>
CDC said that the trade benefits brought about by membership
with ASEAN and AFTA (ASEAN Free Trade Area), the MFN and GSP
privileges and the competitive wage levels were the main reasons
for the foreign direct investments to flow into Cambodia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
