added 20 as the Los Angeles Lakers completed a sweep of their six-
game road trip with a 116-98 victory over Cleveland.
</P>
<P>
The victory, the Lakers' ninth straight overall, put them back
in a tie for the best record in the NBA with Portland at 43-11.
</P>
<P>
Shawn Kemp and Andre Miller each scored 23 points for Cleveland.
</P>
<P>
In New York, Vince Carter had 33 points, nine rebounds and nine
assists to help the Toronto Raptors to a 99-88 victory and second
win over the New York Knicks in nine days. The victory put to a
halt Raptors' three-game losing stread and Nyw York's five-game
home winning advance.
</P>
<P>
Doug Christie added 22 points and Tracy McGrady had 16 for the
Raptors.
</P>
<P>
In Auburn Hills, Michigan, Rik Smits had a season-high 29
points and added nine rebounds as the Pacers beat the Detroit
Pistons 118-111.
</P>
<P>
Reggie Miller and Jalen Rose each scored 23 and Austin Croshere
had 18 points as the Pacers won for the sixth time in seven games.
Mark Jackson had six points and 14 assists.
</P>
<P>
Grant Hill led Detroit with 24 and Lindsey Hunter had 20.
</P>
<P>
In Philadelphia, Allen Iverson scored 22 points as the
Philadelphia 76ers handed the the Los Angeles Clippers their 12th
straight loss, 94-78, and 18th in a row on the road.
</P>
<P>
Toni Kukoc had 18 points and a career-high 14 rebounds. Tyrone
Hill had a season-high 15 points, Theo Ratliff had 13 rebounds and
Eric Snow 11 assists for Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
Lamar Odom had 20 points and nine rebounds, Derek Anderson had
19 points and Maurice Taylor 18 for Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
In Milwaukee, Donyell Marshall had a career-high 37 points and
a season-high 21 rebounds as the Golden State Warriors, playing
without their top three scorers, beat the Milwaukee Bucks 91-86.
</P>
<P>
Erick Dampier added 12 points and 10 rebounds for the Warriors
in their third win in four games with injured Antawn Jamison
abscent.
</P>
<P>
And it was Milwaukee sixth straight homecourt loss. 
</P>
