<HEADLINE> Tonya Harding Arrested for Attacking Live-in Boyfriend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Former American Olympic
figure skater Tonya Harding was arrested in Camas, Washington, on
Tuesday after being accused of throwing a hubcap at her live-in
boyfriend and repeatedly punching him in the face, according to
reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Harding was ordered to appear Thursday in Camas Municipal Court.
</P>
<P>
She was booked Tuesday night for investigation of fourth-degree
domestic violence assault after an altercation that left her
boyfriend Darren Silver's face bruised and bloodied, Camas police
said. She was released an hour later.
</P>
<P>
Harding, 29, and Silver, 28, have lived together for about
three years.
</P>
<P>
According to police, Harding and Silver, both of whom appeared
intoxicated, began fighting Tuesday night in a barn they use as a
garage behind their house. Two men inside the barn told police
officers later that Harding threw a hubcap at Silver, hitting him
in the face, then began punching him.
</P>
<P>
Harding told officers that Silver had held her on the ground
and she hit back to protect herself. 
</P>
