<HEADLINE> Colombia Defeat Peru to Reach Gold Cup Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February (Xinhua) -- With successful efforts from
Arley Dinas and Victor Bonilla, Colombia defeated Peru 2-1 in San
Diego, California on Wednesday to reach the final of the Football
Confederation Gold Cup.
</P>
<P>
The victory helped Colombians move a step closer to their first
title in an international tournament, which will then establish
themselves favored to beat Peru when they meet next month in 2002
World Cup qualifying.
</P>
<P>
Dinas opened the scoring in the 39th minute of the semi-final
game, 11 minutes after he came on as a substitute for Carlos
Asprilla.
</P>
<P>
Bonilla made it 2-0 in the 52nd before Roberto Palacios pulled
one back in the 75th minute as Peru launched fierce offensives on
the Colombian goal.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday Colombia will meet the winner of Thursday's second
semi-final between Trinidad and Tobago and Canada in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
Canada eliminated Mexico with a 2-1 extra time victory last
Sunday. 
</P>
