<HEADLINE> Sino-US Household Appliance Makers Launch Research Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Rongshida, one of China's
leading manufacturers of household electric appliances, and U.S.
electronics firm Maytag have jointly set up a research institute
in Hefei, capital of Anhui Province, to develop state-of-the-art
products for domestic and overseas customers.
</P>
<P>
The institute covers a floor space of 3,600 square meters and
is a huge technology and information center and think-tank. It is
due to go into operation on March 1.
</P>
<P>
Products designed at the center will be sold both domestically
and abroad. A large number of Chinese and overseas experts will
work at the institute.
</P>
<P>
Based in Hefei, Rongshida, also China's biggest producer of
washing machines, and has cooperated with Maytag to make washing
machines, refrigerators, machinery molds and other domestic
electronic appliances.  
