<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yinhe III Super Computers Widely Used </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Yinhe-III super computers are
now widely used all over China.
</P>
<P>
Yinhe-III super computers have supplanted the Yinhe-II model
and were developed by National Defense Science and Technology
University based in Changsha, Hunan Province. Yinhe-III super
computers were official approved in June 1997.
</P>
<P>
Twelve Yinhe super computers, including six Yinhe-III, have
been sold thus far. These computers are frequently used in weather
forecasts, nuclear science research, air dynamic experiments,
petroleum exploration and seismic data processing.
</P>
<P>
The China National Meteorological Observatory is equipped with
two Yinhe-type super computers, including one Yinhe-III. 
</P>
</TEXT>
