<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Real Estate Sector Appeals to Overseas Developers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Overseas real estate
developers are competing for China's vast market and expect to
profit well from their investments.
</P>
<P>
According to Song Chunhua, vice-minister of construction, more
than 5,000 overseas real estate enterprises, or 20 percent of the
country's total, have participated in real estate development in
China.
</P>
<P>
Song said that more than 4 billion yuan in overseas investment
pours into China's real estate development every year. Overseas
real estate developers enjoy a series of preferential policies
which include exemption from investment regulatory taxes, easy
access to raising of funds, and the freedom to remit their gains
abroad after paying relevant taxes.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the investment structure of China's real
estate sector has greatly improved due to the introduction of a
new housing reform policy. Most of the overseas funds have been
channeled into construction of residential housing.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that the real estate industry will shift its focus
from key cities to small and medium-sized cities and towns, and
from coastal areas to China's hinterland.
</P>
<P>
China's housing construction is expected to grow at an annual
rate of 15 percent in the next century. By 2005, China will build
an additional 1.5 billion sq. m of housing in urban areas, 3.5
billion sq. m of housing in rural areas, and renovate 2.9 billion
sq. m of rundown houses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
