<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Deputy Concerned With SOE Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Xu Gui, a team leader of the
Ciyaobao Coal Mine in northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region, is busy gathering information about his fellow workers'
job satisfaction these days.
</P>
<P>
As a deputy to the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC), Xu
will forward the opinions and proposals of industrial workers to
the Ninth NPC Third Session, which begins March 5.
</P>
<P>
Xu, 47, has worked in the coal mine for 30 years. He solicits
the opinions of coal miners during the day and writes his
proposals at night.
</P>
<P>
Based on the comments he received, he suggested at two previous
NPC sessions that the No. Two Power Plant in Ningxia be built and
some small local coal mines be torn down, and all of his ideas
have been accepted.
</P>
<P>
"At the upcoming session, I am going to put forward suggestions
on reforming the state-owned enterprises (SOE), and how the sector
can play its part in the development of western China and protect
the lawful rights and interests of workers," he said.
</P>
<P>
Other proposals he is to put forward include the establishment
of a social security system, legalization of orderly market
competition, and creation of a favorable environment for getting
state-owned enterprises out of financial trouble. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
