<DOCNO> XIE20000224.0261 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Financial Secretary Heralds Enactment of MTR Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Financial
Secretary Donald Tsang welcomed the enactment of the Mass Transit
Railway (MTR) Bill by the Legislative Council Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"From the perspective of enhancing Hong Kong's financial
markets, the listing of MTRC, a high quality and heavily
capitalized company, will add diversity and stability to the stock
market. A successful public offering will clearly help buttress
Hong Kong's status as an international financial center," Tsang
said.
</P>
<P>
The MTR Bill provides the legislative framework to replace the
MTRC as a statutory corporation with a limited liability company,
to be known as MTR Corporation Limited, and to award the MTR
franchise to that company.
</P>
<P>
It also sets out the regulatory framework for the privatized
entity, which serves to balance and safeguard the interests of
both the users and investors.
</P>
<P>
The enactment of the bill is an important step towards the
planned privatization of a minority share of the MTR Corporation (
MTRC) later this year, as announced in the 1999 Budget speech.
</P>
<P>
"The MTRC has built up over the years a reputation, both
locally and internationally, as a government-owned statutory
corporation providing efficient and high quality railway services,
" said Tsang.
</P>
<P>
"It is also one of the very few railways in the world operating
profitably and on prudent commercial principles with no subsidy
from Government. The privatization of the MTRC will offer a prime
opportunity for Hong Kong citizens to participate in the success
of this solid, well managed company with strong growth potential"
Tsang said.
</P>
<P>
Introduction of private ownership will strengthen market
discipline in the running of this world-class railway, on top of
the keen competition from other transport modes that MTRC faces,
promoting even higher levels of efficiency, said a spokesman for
the government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
Privatization will also provide MTRC with the flexibility to
raise equity financing from capital markets through the issue of
new shares. Such enhanced access to capital markets will expand
the range of financing alternatives for MTRC to improve and
develop the railway network, the spokesman said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
