<HEADLINE> 2ndlead: Mayon Volcano Erupts, Top Alert Level Declared (EDS: Updates with top alert level declared.) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The maximum alert level of 5
has been declared on Mayon Volcano at 09:45 a.m. local time (0145
GMT)Thursday following the sighting of magma in its crater and the
upheaval of pyroclastic flow, said the Philippine Institute of
Volcanology and Seismology (Phivolcs).
</P>
<P>
Phivolcs said in a bulletin that at 08:26 a.m. local time (0026
GMT) an explosion type earthquake was recorded, which was followed
3 minutes later by pyroclastic flow pouring down the Bonga Gully
at the southeast side of the mountain.
</P>
<P>
But so far, there was no report on damages or casualties, the
Phivolcs added.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, some 4,000 residents from towns near Mayon Volcano's 7-
kilometer permanent danger zone have flied to evacuation centers
due to the increased volcano activity.
</P>
<P>
The alert level on Mayon Volcano was raised to the top level of
5 only hours after Phivolcs assigned level 4 over Mayon early
Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
According to Phivolcs, alert level 4 means that the volcano
will start spewing lava form the summit, causing lava flows down
the southeastern flanks of the mountain while level 5 indicates
eruption activity.
</P>
<P>
Mayon Volcano, lying about 300 kilometers southeast of Manila,
began to show unstable signs since June 22, 1999 and its latest
major eruption was in 1993, which killed some 70 persons.
</P>
<P>
Mayon volcano, which reaches up to around 2,462 meters above
sea level and has 250 square kilometers in area, has erupted at
least 40 times since 1616.
</P>
<P>
Mt. Mayon is one of 22 most active volcanoes in the Philippines,
a country which has more than 200 volcanoes distributed in its
whole territory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000224.0266 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Closes Tax Loopholes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Board of
Investment(BOI) has introduced new rules to close tax loopholes in
its incentive system in a bid to help raise revenue, the official
Daily News reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Under the new rules appropriate minimum investment limits will
be imposed on all incentive categories to ensure that BOI
incentives are available only for priority sector investment
activities, BOI Chairman Thilan Wijesinghe said.
</P>
<P>
"The BOI hopes to work closely with other government agencies
to ensure revenue collection happens in a systematic and
coordinated manner and to prevent abuses," Wijesinghe was quoted
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Consequently, a Revenue Protection Unit comprising full-time
officers of the BOI, Inland Revenue and Customs departments is to
be set up to strengthen the revenue enforcement laws and prevent
abuse of concessions.
</P>
<P>
Wijesinghe said the new agency will take action to ensure that
revenue due to the government will be collected on a systematic
basis,disputes are expeditiously resolved and computerized
monitoring systems are in place.
</P>
<P>
While incentives for regional industrialization will continue,
a tax holiday of five years and eight years will be granted only
to industries located within a designated industrial park or
export processing zone.
</P>
<P>
The 10-year tax holiday will remain for projects with a total
investment of over 3.5 billion rupees (48 million U.S. dollars) or
flagship projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
