<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Welfare Lottery Popular in Northeast China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Zhang, who works in this
capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province, is addicted to
buying welfare lottery tickets.
</P>
<P>
"I am pleased if I get some small prize--even as little as
fifty yuan (6 US dollars)," Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
To date, about 800 computer lottery ticket sales outlets have
been set up in Shenyang, which has a population of 6.8 million.
</P>
<P>
While Zhang limits herself to only a couple of tickets per week,
some citizens are spending big bucks in hopes of collecting the
top prize.
</P>
<P>
A man surnamed Dai, who sells lottery tickets, said that every
Wednesday, before the winning number is chosen randomly by
computer, long queues of hundreds of people form outside his
office window.
</P>
<P>
And some people see the lottery as something more than a chance
to make a fortune. An elderly couple bought a lottery ticket with
the number 650628 -- the date of their marriage.
</P>
<P>
"We don't care if we win, we just want to recall some beautiful
memories," they said.
</P>
<P>
The lottery is designed to help develop local social welfare
services.  
</P>
</TEXT>
