<HEADLINE> Lack of Wind Forces Postponement of Race 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The 30th America's Cup is
being marred by perfect summer weather.
</P>
<P>
For the second time in the series, racing between Team New
Zealand and Italian challenger Prada was postponed Thursday due to
a lack of consistent wind on the Hauraki Gulf.
</P>
<P>
Race 3 is expected to go ahead Saturday, the fifth scheduled
race day.
</P>
<P>
Team New Zealand has a 2-0 lead in the best-of-nine series.
</P>
<P>
Race committee chairman Harold Bennett decided to postpone the
race Thursday when the crews had been on the water for almost 2 1/
2 hours after the scheduled start time of 1.15 p.m. local time (
0015 GMT).
</P>
<P>
The breeze peaked around eight knots but was considered too
inconsistent to allow match racing.
</P>
<P>
The series opener was postponed last Saturday for 24 hours
because the breeze didn't exceed four knots, until the both teams
left the water.
</P>
<P>
Team New Zealand won the opening race by 1 minute, 17 seconds
last Sunday and, after a non-racing day Monday, returned Tuesday
to clinch a victory by 2 minutes, 43 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Team New Zealand swept the series 5-0 against Dennis Conner's
Young America at San Diego in 1995, becoming only the second non-U.
S. team to win the America's Cup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
