<HEADLINE> East China Province Draws Capital to State Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, February 24 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province,
which ranks third in the country in terms of gross domestic
product, has decided to encourage more individuals, including
overseas investors, to engage in state projects.
</P>
<P>
Wang Renyuan, director of the Shandong Provincial Economic and
Trade Commission, said here recently that all major state projects
to be launched in the province are to absorb capital from various
sources, rather than only from the state.
</P>
<P>
Wang further noted that the decision aims to revitalize the
state sector, which has suffered great losses over the past years.
</P>
<P>
In a major step, the province has announced more than 70 major
state projects open to both domestic and overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
These projects, which will involve new and high technologies,
all have bright prospects, according to Wang.
</P>
<P>
Shandong spent more than 21.6 billion yuan (2.6 billion US
dollars) on key state projects last year.  
</P>
