<HEADLINE> Man Marks Five Years With Transplanted Lung </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Ji Shuchun, a 52-year-old
farmer, celebrated the fifth anniversary of his lung transplant
this week at Anzhen Hospital in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
He considers February 23 a birthday of sorts, as it was exactly
five years ago that Professor Chen Yuping performed the life-
saving operation to transplant a new left lung into Ji.
</P>
<P>
Ji's doctors and nurses celebrated his five-year mark with a
three-layer cake in honor of the man who holds Asia's survival
record for lung transplantation.
</P>
<P>
Ji suffered from fibrosis, a lung disease that makes normal
breathing difficult. Doctors said a transplant was his only hope.
</P>
<P>
He is pleased with the results of his dangerous operation,
saying that this year is the first since 1995 that he has not
needed regular blood transfusions.  
</P>
