<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Manufacturing Sector Reports Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's leading
industrial city, generated 15.7 billion yuan in profits from its
state-owned manufacturers in 1999, up 21 percent from the previous
year.
</P>
<P>
The number of loss-making large and medium-sized state-owned
manufacturers in the city dropped from 310 to 156 last year.
</P>
<P>
Local analysts attributed the upward trend to deepened reform
and accelerated technological upgrading in the manufacturing
sector.
</P>
<P>
More mergers and bankruptcies were reported in industries like
textiles and iron and steel in Shanghai in 1999, reducing the
number of state-owned enterprises in the red by about 16 percent.
</P>
<P>
More state-owned enterprises went public, raising a total of 5.
3 billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
Investment in the technological upgrading of the manufacturing
sector increased by five billion yuan on a yearly basis to reach
11.5 billion yuan in 1999.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
