<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pudong Sees Soaring Foreign Trade in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The Pudong area in east China
's Shanghai City saw its foreign trade volume rise by 108 percent
in January to 1.493 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The import rose 172 percent to 976 million US dollars while the
export grew 43 percent to 517 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 48 percent of the area's export was done
by state-owned enterprises, up 84 percent over the corresponding
period last year. Some 64 percent of its import was done by the
foreign-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Pudong's trade with Japan skyrocketed by 154 percent to 293
million US dollars. Japan is Pudong's largest trading partner.
</P>
</TEXT>
