<HEADLINE> 33 Buried in Landslide in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- At least 33 people were buried
following a landslide in Central Java, Indonesia, on Wednesday
morning, according to the Antara News Agency Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The landslide occurred in the village of Windusari in Brebes in
the northwestern part of the province.
</P>
<P>
Antara quoted a coordination center dealing with the incident
as saying that seven of the victims were dead on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Diggings for the rest of the victims had been stopped that
night for fear of a further landslide due to incessant rains, the
report added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
