<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Coffee Growers of Central America, Mexico to Meet Over Price Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Coffee producers from four
Central American countries and Mexico will meet next Monday in
Guatemala City, Guatemala's capital, to analyze the crisis in this
sector due to a price fall.
</P>
<P>
Producers from Guatemala, El Salvador, Honduras and Nicaragua
are very concerned about the downturn of coffee prices, Guatemala'
s National Association of Coffee (Anacafe) said in a communique
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Mexico's participation will be its first since isthmus coffee
growers started such contacts in May 1988, according to reports
reaching here from Guatemala City.
</P>
<P>
Participants of the meeting will seek ways to check the
worldwide collapse in coffee prices, increase of production costs
and contraction of good crops, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
They will plan regular meetings to unify standards and forge
common policies for a price recovery.
</P>
<P>
According to Anacafe, Central America is the second largest
coffee exporter after Brazil. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
