<HEADLINE> U.S., German Companies Bidding for Construction of Albanian Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, February 23 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. company Brown &AMP; Root
has joined the list of bidders for the construction of Tirana's
new airport terminal by submitting an application to the Ministry
of Transport, ministry sources said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Germany also showed interest in the project. On
Tuesday, German Ambassador in Tirana Peter Kiewit submitted to
Transport Minister Ingrid Shuli a request to allow Siemens and
Lufthansa to take part in the building of the terminal, which will
need an investment of about 30 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Siemens has also submitted several bids to improve the runway,
lighting and hangars at Rinas Airport. The capacity of the airport
is expected to rise to 600,000 persons per year from the current
250,000. 
</P>
