<HEADLINE> Argentine Private Plane Crash Kills Four </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, February 23 (Xinhua) -- A private airplane
crashed in Argentina on Wednesday, leaving its crew of four men
dead.
</P>
<P>
Air Force sources said the accident occurred when a Cesna 402
plane crashed into the side of a hill, 50 kilometers from Salta
city, capital of the Salta province.
</P>
<P>
The wreckage of the burned plane have been found in this
isolated, mountainous area which is covered with dense vegetation,
but rescuers have encountered some difficulty in making contact
with local police.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is reportedly still under
investigation. 
