<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top-seed Halard-Decugis Withdraws from IGA Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Julie Halard-
Decugis of France Wednesday withdrew from the IGA SuperThrift
tennis tournament in Oklahoma city because of a muscle strain.
</P>
<P>
Halard-Decugis, ranked seventh in the world, was scheduled to
open play Wednesday in singles. Instead, qualifying round loser
Meilen Tu of the United States was given her berth in the
tournament and lost 6-4, 3-6,6-2 to Italy's Rita Grande.
</P>
<P>
The injury to Halard-Decugis also ends the tournament for her
doubles partner, Alexandra Stevenson, who was already out of
singles competition.
</P>
<P>
Replacing Halard-Decugis and Stevenson in doubles will be
France's Sarah Pitkowski and Lubomira Bacheva of Bulgaria. The
eighth-seeded Sarah Pitkowski entered her second-round singles
match Wednesday, defeating Slovakia's Daniela Hantuchova 6-2, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, fifth-seeded Natalie Dechy of France
eliminated Australia's Nicole Pratt 6-4, 6-3 and sixth-seeded Lisa
Raymond beat Corina Morariu 2-6, 6-0, 6-3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
