<HEADLINE> Liaoning Uses Huge Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province actually utilized 1.31 billion US dollars of foreign
investment in 1999, more than the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The province signed 1,100 industrial projects with foreign
business people last year, 32 of which involve a total investment
of 20 million US dollars and above each, according to a local
source.
</P>
<P>
The amount of contractual foreign investment reached 2.63
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that one fifth of the world's top 500
enterprises have poured investment into Liaoning, an industrial
base of China.  
</P>
