<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Another Tunnel to Run Through Shanghai's River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Work will soon begin on the
fourth tunnel under the Huangpu River in Shanghai, China's largest
economic center.
</P>
<P>
The tunnel, nearly 3,000 meters long in total, will be put into
operation in 2003, a local source said.
</P>
<P>
The eight-lane tunnel will be built by Shanghai City
Construction Group and Shanghai Waterway Bureau, involving a total
investment of nearly 1.1 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The tunnel will start from Wusong Park in the west and end at
Sancha Port in the east. Experts note that the construction
process will be very complicated.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
