<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Chinese Travel During Spring Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- More Chinese people have used
the seven-day Spring Festival for traveling, with the number of
those going overseas nearly doubling to 140,000, said a survey by
the National Tourism Administration.
</P>
<P>
The survey found that more than 20 million people, a 10 percent
increase over last year's corresponding period, traveled inside
China during the festival period starting from February 5.
</P>
<P>
The survey revealed that about 16.3 billion yuan (1.96 billion
U.S. dollars) was spent on traveling during the seven days, a 16.6
percent growth over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Of the domestic tourists, nearly one fifth traveled by plane or
train to faraway areas. The rest visited sites around where they
live.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
