<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0030 GMT, February 24 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The International Force in East Timor (
INTERFET) was formally replaced by the United Nations peacekeeping
force in Dili, UN spokesman Fred Eckhard said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
UN Transitional Administrator Sergo Vieira de Mello, INTERFET
Commander General Peter Cosgrove and UN Force Commander Jaime de
los Santos signed a declaration on the replacement of INTERFET,
Eckhard said. (UN-East Timor)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Israeli occupation forces in south Lebanon shelled
Wednesday afternoon areas in the western sector of south Lebanon,
but no casualties were reported.
</P>
<P>
Reports from inside the occupied zone said that the Israeli
troops also arrested a Lebanese citizen, Nimer Farghal, 48, and
his daughter Sawsan, 27, who were led to the al-khayam detention
camp. But the reports did not give reasons for the arrest. (
Lebanon-Israel)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi said on
Wednesday that his country will work seriously in line with the
policy of detente, dialogue and confidence-building in foreign
relations.
</P>
<P>
On the impact of Iran's 6th parliamentary election on the
country's foreign policy, Kharrazi said Iran has given priority to
cooperation with neighboring states and regional countries and
will proceed with strengthening a sense of brotherhood and
solidarity in the region.  (Iran-Detente Policy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Britain's Northern Ireland Secretary Peter
Mandelson Wednesday called on the Clinton administration to help
revitalize the peace process on the British province's future.
</P>
<P>
However, both Mandelson and former U.S. Senator George Mitchell,
who mediated the landmark Good Friday Accords in 1998, ruled out
Mitchell's return to direct mediation. (US-UK-N.Ireland Peace)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States and France said on Wednesday
that NATO countries are considering additional forces to the
Yugoslav province of Kosovo to keep peace there after fighting
erupted between the peacekeeping force and local Kosovars.
</P>
<P>
Visiting French Defense Minister Alain Richard and U.S. Defense
Secretary William Cohen made the announcement at a press
conference following their meeting focusing on the development in
Kosovo. (NATO-Kosovo) 
</P>
