<HEADLINE> Argentine Stocks Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, February 23 (Xinhua) -- The leading Merval index
on the Buenos Aires Exchange closed higher at 626.69 points on
Wednesday, up 0.83 percent compared with Tuesday's 621.47 points.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 34.428 million U.S. dollars against Tuesday's
32.876 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The annual inter-bank interest rate increased to 7.65 percent
from 7.35 percent in the 24-hour term. The exchange rate of the
Argentine peso against the dollar stood at 0.996 for purchase and
1.001 for sale. 
</P>
