</P>
<P>
-- Japanese Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi on Wednesday defended
his aide in a stock scandal and vowed to give the country's
economy priority over fiscal health in a new direct debate session
with opposition leaders in the parliament.
</P>
<P>
-- Japan's Finance Ministry will open the way for banks to sell
policies offered by insurance companies at their branches starting
in April 2001. 
