<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Heptathlon world champion Eunice
Barber of France pulled out of next weekend's European indoor
athletics championships in Ghent because of a thigh injury, French
team manager Richard Descoux said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Descoux said Barber still needed to nurse her injury for a
complete fitness for the Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Barber had been expected to take part in the long jump and the
pentathlon in Ghent. 
