<HEADLINE> Swiss Coach Sent Off as UAE Win 1-0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARIRO, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Swiss coach and captain both
were sent off as the United Arab Emirates won 1-0 on Wednesday in
a four-nation soccer tournament in Muscat, Oman.
</P>
<P>
In the other match, Oman lost 4-0 to Slovenia though Slovenian
defender Spasoje Bulajic was also shown red card on the hour.
</P>
<P>
Swiss interim coach Hans-Peter Zaugg was expelled just two
minutes from start when he argued with the referee for tackling.
</P>
<P>
Captain Stephane Henchoz left the field in the 42nd minute
before UAE's Mohamed Ibrahim was sent off in the 68th minute.
</P>
<P>
Ali Aloo Haider scored the winning goal in the 85th minute.
</P>
