<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Joint Efforts to End Illegal Immigration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- China will continue working
with Australia to stop illegal immigrations and the notorious "
snakeheads" who smuggle Chinese people overseas, according to a
China Daily report today.
</P>
<P>
China and Australia have successfully cooperated over the past
year on the immigration problem and the repatriation of stowaways,
said Guo Xiqin, deputy director of the Frontier Administration
Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, 1,300 illegal migration cases from inland China were
found by Chinese frontier police and more than 9,000 stowaways
were captured.
</P>
<P>
The frontier police arrested more than 800 illegal immigration
organizers, colloquially called "snakeheads", last year.
</P>
<P>
Eight boasts carrying 544 Chinese illegal immigrants were
captured in Australia last year and all of them were repatriated
to China, according to Andrew Metcalfe, deputy secretary of the
Australian Department of Immigration and Multiculural Affairs.
</P>
<P>
The Australian deputy secretary arrived in Beijing on Sunday
for talks with Chinese government officials on areas of
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
A large-scale publicity campaign was launched in China and
Australia informing people that stowaways were victims of
snakeheads and would gain nothing by illegal immigration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
