<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Launches Postcard Promotion for 2006 World Cup Bid  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, February 23 (Xinhua) -- The German Football Federation
(DFB) launched a nationwide postcard campaign to seek for support
for the bid to host the 2006 World Cup Football Championship.
</P>
<P>
23.3 million postcards will be sent by the DFB to households
throughout Germany asking them to fill in a reply card answering
which teams they would prefer to see at the 2006 World Cup.
</P>
<P>
Then the postcards will be collected in Frankfurt and sent to
the every federations of 2006 World Cup aspirants in mid-June.
</P>
<P>
At present there are five countries bidding to host the 2006
World Cup, they are Brazil, England, Morocco and South Africa
besides Germany. The executive board of the FIFA will decide on
July 6, 2000 in Zurich, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Germany is very confident of its success. Franz Beckenbauer,
the Football Emperor and the chaiman of the German bidding
committee of 2006 World Cup, has made many tours around the world
and he visited the People's Republc of China, Japan and South
Korea last December and this January he went still to Africa to
drum up for support. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
