<HEADLINE> Heskey Shines in England vs Argentina Friendly  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Emile Heskey produced an eye-
catching display up front in his full debut as England impressed
in their "friendly" against old foes Argentina at Wembley on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Kevin Keegan's side, which included a number of fringe players
keen to cement a Euro 2000 place, had the better of the rematch
with the team that knocked them out of the last World Cup in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Argentina, rated by Keegan as the second best team in the world
behind Brazil, rarely threatened and England did much to dispel
the memories of their last performance, an awful 1-0 defeat by
arch rivals Scotland, with a spirited, inventive display.
</P>
<P>
Heskey's pace and power proved dangerous throughout - and the
Leicester youngster eclipsed some world-class players on his full
debut.
</P>
<P>
Many pundits had questioned the inclusion of Heskey alongside
Alan Shearer up front, but he was given a standing ovation when he
was replaced with 10 minutes left.
</P>
<P>
Andy Cole, one of five England substitutes to come on, tested
Pablo Cavallero 10 minutes from time with his first touch but it
was a rare second half opening for the hosts.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Kily Gonzalez went closest for the visitors with a
low shot saved by David Seaman after 56 minutes and another that
fizzed past a post in the 76th.
</P>
<P>
Both sides wore black armbands following the death of England
great Sir Stanley Matthews at the age of 85. 
</P>
</TEXT>
