<HEADLINE> Dutch Economic Growth Totals 3.5 Percent in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Economic growth in the
Netherlands in 1999 totaled 3.5 percent, according to a survey of
economic conditions published Thursday by the Dutch government.
</P>
<P>
The figure is virtually the same as a year before. The survey
said 1999 was the fourth year in a row with growth in excess of 3
percent.
</P>
<P>
The 3 percent growth level last occurred in the early 1970s,
the survey said.
</P>
<P>
The growth of domestic individual consumption amounted last
year to 3.6 percent and, despite a very small decline, remains
high in comparison with earlier years. 
</P>
