<HEADLINE> Portuguese Literature to Be Focus of Paris Book Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Portuguese literature will be
the focus of the 20th Paris Book Fair to be held from March 17 to
22, said organizers Thursday.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 Portuguese writers will be invited to the book
fair and give signatures on their books, which cover products of
all trends of thoughts and styles from the country's literary
circle.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the so-called "electronic books" will also be a
prominent part of the book fair, which expects 220,000 readers and
from 1,500 to 2,000 writers to visit its exhibition center at the
Porte de Versailles in southern Paris. 
</P>
</TEXT>
