<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Declares State of Disaster in 3 Provinces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe has declared a state
of disaster in the three provinces of Manicaland, Masvingo and
Matabeleland South following the catastrophic effects of cyclone
Eline.
</P>
<P>
The death toll has risen to five and the damage caused is
estimated at millions of U.S. dollars, Local Government and
National Housing Minister John Nkomo told a news conference on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He said that an international appeal for aid has been launched
for the thousands of people lefthe damage that saw homes and granaries
being washed away.
</P>
<P>
The storms and floods wreaked havoc on infrastrud command posts.
</P>
