<HEADLINE> Severe Drought Predicted in North-Eastern Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The north-eastern region of
Rwanda is expected to face severe drought in the next three months
fe westerlies that blow off Rwanda's north-eastern region
and some parts of the east which has led to aridity in those
areas," Musoni Didace, director of Meteorological Department in
the Ministry of Transport and Communications, was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
He said the off-shore westerlies have caused long droughts
called La Nina, which is excessive sunshine.
</P>
<P>
According to a special statement from the meteorological
department of the country, the rains expected in those areas will
be below average over the past 30 years.
</P>
<P>
Didace warned that unless farmers plant early and plant drought
 resistant plants, they may face even more severe conditions in
the next three months due to aridity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
