<HEADLINE> Italian, Algerian FM Find Much Common Ground </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Italy and Algeria must continue
to work towards bolstering dialogue between the two shores of the
Mediterranean, Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini and his
visiting Algerian counterpart Youcef Yousfi agreed in talks here
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers also signed two agreements in order to give
greater continuity and regularity to bilateral relations, a
statement from the Italian Foreign Minister said Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
Dini, in expressing his satisfaction over the positive outcome
of the negotiations, stressed the central role these agreements
will have in combating illegal migration and regulating authorized
immigration.
</P>
<P>
Both Dini and Yousfi also agreed on the need to expand the
agreement to take into account seasonal employment.
</P>
<P>
During today's talks, the minister added, Dini voiced his
satisfaction over the progress made in following up the
commitments made during Bouteflika visit, in particular towards
Italy's participation in Algeria's development and privatization
plans, collaboration in such sectors as energy, agriculture and
the food industry, training, management, heavy industry and
construction.
</P>
<P>
Looking at the Mediterranean, the two diplomatic chiefs found
common ground on the importance of the Mediterranean Forum, which
meet next in march, and Dini expressed the hope that the
conditions will exist for Libya's participation.
</P>
<P>
Yousfi expressed the hope that collaboration with Italy will
serve as an important element in bolstering Algeria's relations
with the European Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
