<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU, CAN Agree on Future Trade Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VILAMOURA, Portugal, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The European Union,
(EU) and the Community of Andean Nations (CAN) have agreed in
principle to negotiations aiming at an economic and commercial
association between the two blocs.
</P>
<P>
The agreement came about Wednesday at the end of a two-day
ministerial meeting between the EU and the CAN in the Portuguese
tourist city of Vilamoura, according to a joint communique issued
Thursday by the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Gunner Wiegand, advisor to the European Commissar for Foreign
Affairs Christopher Patten, said that the EU acknowledged the CAN
request for the strengthening and stabilization of the commercial
system and the relations between the two blocs.
</P>
<P>
The EU-CAN meeting was presided over by the European Trio (
Portugal, France, and Finland) and by the European Council general
secretary, the Spaniard Javier Solanaa, and the foreign ministers
of the South American block (Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador, Peru and
Venezuela.)
</P>
<P>
Wiegand said that the process of negotiations that the EU will
start soon with the Community of Andean Nations will follow the
advances with the Southern Common Market (Mercosur), made up of
Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay, and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
The agreement foresees a technical study for a precise
diagnosis of the existing difficulties and the solution outlook,
added Wiegand.
</P>
<P>
The EU and the CAN said about particular situations that they
support democracy in Ecuador and peace in Colombia.
</P>
<P>
European Union and Latin American nations are seeking to deepen
economic and political ties during the three days of talks which
began Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Community of Andean Nations or the Group Andino is composed
by Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador, Peru and Venezuela. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
